# Grow — core guardrails

- Read `phases.txt` before new features, schema, or analytics logic.
- Build Phase 0 → 1 → 2 → 3 in order. No Phase 3 until Phase 2 is trustworthy on real data.
- Solo personal app first — avoid generic-user abstractions and out-of-scope features (social, streaks, badges, nutrition, iOS).
- Minimize diff scope; match existing patterns once scaffold exists.
- Do not commit `.env`, Supabase keys, or credentials.
- Do not create git commits unless the user asks.
